org.jeo.data

Interface Disposable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Dataset, RasterDataset, TileDataset, VectorDataset, Workspace
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CSVDataset, Disposer, GDALDataset, GeoJSONDataset, GeoPkgDataset, GeoPkgTileSet, GeoPkgVector, GeoPkgWorkspace, Handle, MemRaster, MemTileDataset, MemVector, MemWorkspace, MongoDataset, MongoWorkspace, OGR, OGRDataset, OGRWorkspace, PostGISDataset, PostGISWorkspace, SingleWorkspace

    public interface Disposable
extends Closeable
    Interface for objects that should be closed after usage.

    Such objects typically hold onto resources such as file handles, database connections, etc..

    This interface extends from Closeable but overrides the close() to ensure no IOException is thrown.

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, OpenGeo

      void close()

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
        Disposes the object.

        Unlike Closeable.close() this method does not throw IOException and implementations must ensure no exceptions are thrown from this method.

        Application code must always be sure to call this method on any implementing class. Implementing classes should handle multiple calls to this method.

        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
